		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://today.uic.edu/?p=93799</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[As students get ready to graduate, Career Services provides virtual appointments, resources]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="pf-content">
<div class="wp-block-image"><figure class="alignright size-medium"><img src="https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-387x258.jpg" alt="woman typing" class="wp-image-67820" srcset="https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-387x258.jpg 387w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-768x512.jpg 768w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-590x393.jpg 590w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-1000x667.jpg 1000w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-500x333.jpg 500w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-300x200.jpg 300w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash-1320x880.jpg 1320w, https://today.uic.edu/files/2018/07/kaitlyn-baker-422999-unsplash.jpg 1800w" sizes="(max-width: 387px) 100vw, 387px" /></figure></div>



<p>As students get ready to graduate next month, UIC Career Services is offering its services virtually to help with their job searches</p>



<p>“With the unpredictable future of the job market, it is now more important than ever to prepare and be &#8216;career ready&#8217; for candidates as they seek employment opportunities,” said Jaime Velasquez, associate director of employee relations for UIC Career Services.</p>



<p>“Apart from having a well-written résumé and cover letter, it will be even more important for seniors to network and utilize every resource available to them.&#8221;</p>



<p>Career Services is offering virtual appointments by emailing <a href="mailto:careerservices@uic.edu">careerservices@uic.edu</a>. Virtual walk-ins also are available for reviewing réumés and cover letters or for general career questions between 8:30 a.m.-5 p.m. Monday-Friday by email. </p>



<p>UIC Career Services has a variety of <a href="https://careerservices.uic.edu/">online resources</a> available, including a spring career readiness checklist; the <a href="https://files.webservices.illinois.edu/9106/finaladvisingguide.pdf">2020 Recruiter Career Search Advising Guide</a>, which features advice from recruiters who have been on campus recently, and recordings of recent webinars on topics such as being a job candidate during a recession, virtual networking, and more.</p>



<p>“Above all, we would like to remind seniors that there are still many active job opportunities available to them at <a href="http://uiccareers.com/">uiccareers.com</a> and that we are available to assist them with any career-related question or concern that they may have,” Velasquez said.</p>
